PIGMENTATION OF CLEARED SPECIMENS ON SLIDE. Body generally membranous, pale to yellow; ANT brown with pale ANT I–II and basal part of ANT III; coxae and trochanters pale; femora yellow with light brown distal ends; tibiae brown with paler middle section or pale with only distal part darker; tarsi light brown; SIPH yellow with light brown to brown distal ends; cauda pale (
Fig. 1a
).
